review:
Hello everyone who is reading this review. Where did I start? When open the game before the Menù there is a cutscene that do as an opening for the game. We can see the good graphic (for those titles it need a good graphic) with Anime style drawing. But 1° error, if you have a good view you can see the pixel. The game has got three difficult (Easy-Normal-Hard) mode:
-Free Mode where you can choose and challenge one of all the 22 characters;
-Arcade mode where you can choose the characters, but it is longer because you have to challenge a series (5 challengers) of characters, and you can choose only the characters that you want to use;
-Story Mode that is similal to the Arcade Mode, but it has got the story and reward like image, music and voice.
The gameplay is a bit rich. Every characters has three songs, for a total of 66 songs in the game. Probably other Rythm Game has more songs to play (and all of them are good, some of them more and some of them lesser). If you're searching something horny and... you understand... I'll give you this advice: because of the nature of a Rythm Game if you want to win you have to stay concentrate to the Note's bar, so you can't watch all the curves of the game. The game (like all the Senran Kagura Series) has another feature: the Dressing Room, where you can personalize the characters with all the dressing you gained (Outfit, Accessories, Hairstyle and... Lingerie) and do... something weird for the victim... After that, the game is a bit good. I reccomend it? Yes, but only if you are a Senran Kagura fan (and optionally during a discount). The game is too much expensive for only this (it's not bad but it might be better).
